```plantuml
@startuml TestHaters_ctflow
skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #ffffff
  BorderColor black
  Style roundrect
}
left to right direction

actor User

rectangle "VS Code Extension" as Extension #lightblue {
  rectangle "CtFlowEditorProvider" as EditorProvider #lightcyan
  rectangle "VS Code API" as VSCodeAPI #lightgrey
}

rectangle "Webview UI" as WebviewUI #lightyellow {
  rectangle "React UI" as ReactUI #lightgoldenrodyellow
  rectangle "Node Components" as NodeComponents #lightgoldenrodyellow
  rectangle "Graph Compiler" as GraphCompiler #lightgoldenrodyellow
}

rectangle "Cypress" as Cypress #palegreen

rectangle "Firebase" as Firebase #lightcoral

' ========== Connections ==========
User --> Extension : Open VS Code\nand use extension

Extension --> WebviewUI : Load webview UI
ReactUI --> NodeComponents : Render and manage\nnodes and edges
NodeComponents --> Firebase : Record/replay actions\npotentially using Firebase

EditorProvider --> VSCodeAPI : Register custom editor\nand commands

User --> WebviewUI : Drag-and-drop nodes\nto create test flows
WebviewUI --> GraphCompiler : Compile visual flow\ninto Cypress code

GraphCompiler --> Cypress : Execute compiled\nCypress test code
@enduml
```